            <h3 class="title is-4">What is this site?</h3>
            <p>
                NMAC is a lightweight dashboard for live stream creators who need to quickly review and act on super
                chats and other donation-like events. It emphasizes clarity, fast filtering, and spreadsheet-like
                scanning so important messages are not missed during or after a broadcast.
            </p>

            <h3 class="title is-4 mt-5">A one-person labor of love</h3>
            <p>
                This project is the work of one developer. It is designed, coded, tested, and operated by a
                single maintainer while balancing other responsibilities. Features ship incrementally, and priorities
                are strongly shaped by practical creator workflow feedback.
            </p>

            <article class="notification has-background-primary-soft has-text-primary-bold">
                <strong>Please know:</strong> this is a grassroots, one-person project. Your support, whether reporting
                a bug, suggesting an idea, contributing code, or helping with hosting costs, makes a tangible
                difference.
            </article>

            <h3 class="title is-4 mt-5">Why support?</h3>
            <p>
                Hosting, monitoring, storage, backups, and third-party APIs all cost money. As usage grows, those costs
                grow too. If NMAC helps your creator workflow, support helps keep development sustainable and reliability
                high.
            </p>

